facebook_team?":false,"team_private?":false,"vulnerability_information":"## Summary:\n\nThe Linux binaries `nordvpn` and `nordvpnd` don't have PIE/ASLR enabled. A such feature is used to harden programs against the exploitation of memory corruption bugs and should be enabled.\n\nThe use of ASLR has long been debated among the Golang community. However, it seems that it's becoming the default choice now.\n\n## Steps To Reproduce:\n\n```\n$ rabin2 -I /usr/bin/nordvpn | grep pic\npic      false\n$ rabin2 -I /usr/sbin/nordvpnd | grep pic\npic      false\n```\n\n## Supporting Material/References:\n\n  * https://insanitybit.github.io/2016/12/28/golang-and-rustlang-memory-safety\n  * https://github.com/golang/go/issues/35192\n  * https://fedoraproject.org/wiki/Changes/golang-buildmode-pie\n\n## Impact\n\nAny memory corruption bug (e.g. buffer overflow) can easily lead to a working exploit when ASLR is not enabled.","vulnerability_information_html":"\u003ch2 id=\"summary\"\u003eSummary:\u003c/h2\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eThe Linux binaries \u003ccode\u003enordvpn\u003c/code\u003e and \u003ccode\u003enordvpnd\u003c/code\u003e don\u0026#39;t have PIE/ASLR enabled. A such feature is used to harden programs against the exploitation of memory corruption bugs and should be enabled.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eThe use of ASLR has long been debated among the Golang community. However, it seems that it\u0026#39;s becoming the default choice now.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003ch2 id=\"steps-to-reproduce\"\u003eSteps To Reproduce:\u003c/h2\u003e\n\u003cdiv class=\"highlight\"\u003e\u003cpre class=\"highlight plaintext\"\u003e\u003ccode\u003e$ rabin2 -I /usr/bin/nordvpn | grep pic\npic      false\n$ rabin2 -I /usr/sbin/nordvpnd | grep pic\npic      false\n\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/pre\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\n\u003ch2 id=\"supporting-material-references\"\u003eSupporting Material/References:\u003c/h2\u003e\n\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003ca title=\"https://insanitybit.github.io/2016/12/28/golang-and-rustlang-memory-safety\" href=\"/redirect?url=https%3A%2F%2Finsanitybit.github.io%2F2016%2F12%2F28%2Fgolang-and-rustlang-memory-safety\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\"\u003e\u003cspan\u003ehttps://insanitybit.github.io/2016/12/28/golang-and-rustlang-memory-safety\u003c/span\u003e\u003ci class=\"icon-external-link\"\u003e\u003c/i\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003ca title=\"https://github.com/golang/go/issues/35192\" href=\"/redirect?url=https%3A%2F%2Fgithub.com%2Fgolang%2Fgo%2Fissues%2F35192\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\"\u003e\u003cspan\u003ehttps://github.com/golang/go/issues/35192\u003c/span\u003e\u003ci class=\"icon-external-link\"\u003e\u003c/i\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003ca title=\"https://fedoraproject.org/wiki/Changes/golang-buildmode-pie\" href=\"/redirect?url=https%3A%2F%2Ffedoraproject.org%2Fwiki%2FChanges%2Fgolang-buildmode-pie\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\"\u003e\u003cspan\u003ehttps://fedoraproject.org/wiki/Changes/golang-buildmode-pie\u003c/span\u003e\u003ci class=\"icon-external-link\"\u003e\u003c/i\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\n\u003ch2 id=\"impact\"\u003eImpact\u003c/h2\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eAny memory corruption bug (e.g. buffer overflow) can easily lead to a working exploit when ASLR is not enabled.\u003c/p\u003e\n","weakness":{"id":57,"name":"Violation of Secure Design Principles"},"original_report_id":null,"original_report_url":null,"attachments":[],"allow_singular_disclosure_at":null,"vote_count":3,"voters":["probatorem","what_web","sl33pyp0t4t0"],"severity":{"rating":"none","author_type":"Team"},"structured_scope":{"databaseId":46628,"asset_type":"DOWNLOADABLE_EXECUTABLES","asset_identifier":"Linux Executable","max_severity":"medium"},"abilities":{"assignable_team_members":[],"assignable_team_member_groups":[]},"can_edit_custom_fields_attributes":false,"activities":[{"id":7324842,"is_inter